      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:4:55:3",
      "text": [
        " قُلْتُ لِأَبِي عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) مَا لِلرَّجُلِ يُعَاقِبُ بِهِ مَمْلُوكَهُ فَقَالَ عَلَى قَدْرِ ذَنْبِهِ قَالَ فَقُلْتُ فَقَدْ عَاقَبْتَ حَرِيزاً بِأَعْظَمَ مِنْ جُرْمِهِ فَقَالَ وَيْلَكَ هُوَ مَمْلُوكٌ لِي وَ إِنَّ حَرِيزاً شَهَرَ السَّيْفَ وَ لَيْسَ مِنِّي مَنْ شَهَرَ السَّيْفَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hammad, from Al Halby, from Abu Al Abbas who said, ",
          "‘I said to Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup>, ‘What is for the man he can punish his slave with?’ So he<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘Upon the measurement of his sin’. So I said, ‘So I have punished Hareza with greater than his offence’. So he<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘Woe be unto you! He was a slave of mine<sup>asws</sup>, and Hareyz brandished the sword, and the one who brandishes the sword is not from me<sup>asws</sup>’."
        ]
      }
    }
